          Title: Sr Full Stack .NET Engineer (Production Support Team)

          Need only support, maintenance and heavy debugging of existing applications

          Debugging application on a Production Server

          Encompass manual debugging, manual troubleshooting and the continuous maintenance of application systems, programs, services, and otherassociated software components, tailored to meet the demands of the enterprise, particularly addressing tasks of moderate to high complexity.

          There will be no new development involved just the enhancement, maintenance, and resolution of complex issues within existing legacy .NET applications. Must be a fundamentally sound and skilled Full Stack .NET Developer comfortable supporting applications that have been previously developed, demonstrating the capability to learn different systems and code bases quickly.

          Requirements

          • Essential qualifications for this role include a minimum of 10 years of hands-on experience working in the US as a Full Stack .NET Developer.
          • Recent (most recent 5 years) and demonstrable expertise in the manual debugging and troubleshooting of web-based applications in production, as well as a demonstrated ability to perform maintenance and enhancements on existing/legacy applications using: Net 4.0/3.5/2.9, MVC 4.0 - 5.0, Asp.net Core 2.0, Kendo UI, ADO.Net 4.0/3.5/2.0/1.1, LINQ, Entity, C#, N-Tier, Java Scripts, jQuery, HTML, CSS, WCF, WPF and WCF Services, ASP.Net Web Forms and MVC, ASP.Net State Management, ASP.Net Caching, ASP.Net Web Applications, MS SQL Server 2008-2019, T-SQL, Stored Procedures, Joins, Tables, Functions, dnSpy, CLR
          • Expert-level experience resolving: Connectivity issues, Access Issues, performance Issues, storage issues, and data retrieval issues.
          • Strong ability to learn, analyze, and resolve issues surrounding multiple applications with different code bases
          • Manual Debugging without using Visual Studio
          • ServiceDesk ticketing system experience a plus

          • Seniority level

            Mid-Senior level

          • Employment type

            Full-time

          • Job function

            Engineering and Information Technology

          • Industries

            IT Services and IT Consulting
